But she discovers too late that the “young master” she has to serve is the empire’s foolish prince, Leone Atarta. The novel’s author must’ve misspelled the word “feral” as Leone turns out to be much more of a beast than a simple beauty. And thus begins Trixie’s tale of trying to tame her new “dog” and make him the shining crown prince he’s meant to be.\n\n---\n**Official Translations:**\n* [Chinese (Simplified) / 汉语](https://www.kuaikanmanhua.com/web/topic/16794)\n* [Chinese (Traditional) / 漢語](https://tw.kakaowebtoon.com/content/%E7%8B%97%E7%8B%97%E7%9A%87%E5%AD%90%E5%9F%B9%E8%82%B2%E6%B3%95/572)\n* [French / Français](https://www.tappytoon.com/fr/book/crowning-my-feral-prince-fr)\n* [German / Deutsch](https://www.tappytoon.com/de/book/crowning-my-feral-prince-de)\n* [Indonesian / Bahasa Indonesia](https://www.webtoons.com/id/romantic-fantasy/how-to-place-my-dog-on-the-throne/list?title_no=4620)\n* [Japanese / 日本語](https://piccoma.com/web/product/124964)\n* [Thai / ภาษาไทย](https://www.webtoons.com/th/romantic-fantasy/how-to-place-my-dog-on-the-throne/list?title_no=4805)","fr":"Lorsque les gens se réveillent dans un roman, c'est généralement pour eux le début d'incroyables aventures pleines de découvertes et d'épanouissement personnel... mais pour Trixie Guiseppe, on est loin du compte.
